WESTERN Cape Police have launched the 72 hour activation plan to
probe the circumstances that left three males with fatal gunshot wounds in
Citrusdal. Police spokesman Colonel Andrè Traut said, during the early hours
of Saturday morning, 16 July 2022 the three victims, all believed to be Lesotho
nationals were shot and killed at their informal dwelling in Riverview. “It is believed that a fourth male also sustained a gunshot wound,
but managed to escape the attack. This victim is yet to be traced. The suspect
or suspects fled the scene and are yet to be apprehended.” READ: Alex shootings leave five dead! Colonel Traut said the motive
for the murders are not yet established. “Any person who can shed light on the matter is encouraged to
contact Crime Stop on 08600 10111 or use the mobile application My SAPS.
Callers may remain anonymous,” he said.